# Universal Workflow Invocation

## Purpose

Any development request **automatically** runs the full autonomous engineering pipeline. The user never manually invokes planning, testing, review, validation, debugging, or documentation.

## Single Command Surface

Describe work normally. Examples:

| User says | Pipeline runs |
|-----------|---------------|
| Build X | Full pipeline |
| Fix Y | Full pipeline |
| Refactor Z | Full pipeline |
| Investigate A | Full pipeline |
| Improve B | Full pipeline |
| Optimize C | Full pipeline |
| Any coding task | Full pipeline |

**No workflow keywords required.**

## Mandatory Pipeline (All Phases)

```
1. ANALYZE      → Read codebase, rules, affected files
2. PLAN         → Orchestrator: requirements, decomposition, validation criteria
3. ROUTE        → Select roles per 06-role-routing.mdc
4. IMPLEMENT    → Implementation Specialist (Orchestrator does not bulk-implement)
5. VALIDATE     → Build, typecheck, tests, smoke checks
6. REVIEW       → Review Specialist + Orchestrator final review
7. DEBUG        → If validation/review fails → Debugging Specialist
8. REVALIDATE   → Re-run validation (max 10 cycles per 02-validation-loops.mdc)
9. DOCUMENT     → Documentation Specialist if behavior/structure changed
10. APPROVE     → Orchestrator completion gate only (99-completion-gate.mdc)
```

**Never skip phases. Never stop after IMPLEMENT.**

## Phase → Role Mapping

| Phase | Role |
|-------|------|
| Analyze, Plan, Route, Approve | Orchestrator |
| Implement | Implementation Specialist |
| Validate (tests) | Testing Specialist |
| Review (pre-approval) | Review Specialist |
| Debug | Debugging Specialist |
| Revalidate | Implementation or Debugging Specialist |
| Document | Documentation Specialist |
| Parallel subtasks | Parallel Execution Specialist |

## Default Validation (This Repository)

Run automatically after IMPLEMENT:

```bash
npm run build
npx tsc --noEmit
```

Additional when applicable: browser check (UI), section ID/nav verification, test runner.

## Prohibited Shortcuts

- Do not ask "should I run the build?" — **always run it**
- Do not ask "should I create a plan?" — **always plan first**
- Do not ask "should I delegate?" — **always delegate execution**
- Do not mark complete on generation alone
- Do not use prohibited completion phrases (see `99-completion-gate.mdc`)

## Completion Response

**Complete:**
```
## Status: COMPLETE
### Requirements / Validation / Review / Evidence / Documentation
```

**Incomplete:**
```
## Status: INCOMPLETE
### Blocker / Next step
```
